"{\"uid\": \"forbes.com-sites-mikeosullivan-2024-07-25-france-agrees-to-a-political-truce-as-the-olympics-approaches\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"ByMike O'Sullivan,  Former Contributor.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 39, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"French president Emmanuel Macron has declared that he will wait till after the Olympics to form a government, partly we suspect in the hope that he also hopes for the Nouveau Front Populaire (NFP) grouping to come apart.\", \"from\": 41, \"to\": 261, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 41, \"end\": 57, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French president\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 58, \"end\": 73, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 216, \"end\": 231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Popular_Front_(France)\", \"score\": 0.9829156082440914, \"rank\": 0.01738050900062388, \"text\": \"Front Populaire\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Popular_Front_(France)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Popular_Front_(France)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Specifically, he has called for a political 'truce' during the Olympics.\", \"from\": 262, \"to\": 334, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Indeed, in the last week there are signs of new coalition dynamics.\", \"from\": 335, \"to\": 402, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Importantly, Ya\\u00ebl-Braun-Pivet has been re-elected as the speaker of the Assembly in a vote where the NFP and Republicans have supported her, and where the NFP have garnered 12 of 22 positions in the Assembly (like the committee chairship in the Senate etc - the NFP have two Assembly vice-presidents and the chair of the finance committee).\", \"from\": 404, \"to\": 744, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 476, \"end\": 484, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deliberative_assembly\", \"score\": 0.996577430436766, \"rank\": 0.0029697717684148495, \"text\": \"Assembly\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deliberative_assembly\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deliberative_assembly\"}, {\"begin\": 505, \"end\": 508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Federation_Party\", \"score\": 0.9999953416392418, \"rank\": 3.840724037003097e-06, \"text\": \"NFP\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Federation_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Federation_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 513, \"end\": 524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republicanism\", \"score\": 0.9998635936559064, \"rank\": 0.00013361237032698205, \"text\": \"Republicans\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republicanism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republicanism\"}, {\"begin\": 559, \"end\": 562, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Federation_Party\", \"score\": 0.9999953416392418, \"rank\": 3.840724037003097e-06, \"text\": \"NFP\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Federation_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Federation_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 603, \"end\": 611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deliberative_assembly\", \"score\": 0.996577430436766, \"rank\": 0.0029697717684148495, \"text\": \"Assembly\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deliberative_assembly\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deliberative_assembly\"}, {\"begin\": 649, \"end\": 655, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Senate\", \"score\": 0.6270421836473927, \"rank\": 0.5430461360401726, \"text\": \"Senate\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Senate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Senate\"}, {\"begin\": 666, \"end\": 669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Federation_Party\", \"score\": 0.9999953416392418, \"rank\": 3.840724037003097e-06, \"text\": \"NFP\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Federation_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Federation_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 679, \"end\": 687, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deliberative_assembly\", \"score\": 0.996577430436766, \"rank\": 0.0029697717684148495, \"text\": \"Assembly\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deliberative_assembly\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deliberative_assembly\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Of note also, is a pact of sorts between Gabriel Attal - now leader of the Macronist party, and Laurent Wauquiez - leader of the centrist Republicans.\", \"from\": 745, \"to\": 895, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 786, \"end\": 799, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gabriel Attal\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\"}, {\"begin\": 883, \"end\": 894, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republicanism\", \"score\": 0.9998635936559064, \"rank\": 0.00013361237032698205, \"text\": \"Republicans\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republicanism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republicanism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wauquiez is seen by many of the centre right as a potential presidential hopeful.\", \"from\": 896, \"to\": 977, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The close relationship between them, points to an emerging ploy which to paraphase the former Interior minister Gerard Darmanin aims to 'to break the socialists away from the NFP'.\", \"from\": 979, \"to\": 1159, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1073, \"end\": 1090, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interior_minister\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7639182667365908e-23, \"text\": \"Interior minister\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interior_minister\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interior_minister\"}, {\"begin\": 1091, \"end\": 1097, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barksdale_Organization\", \"score\": 0.9993079690949, \"rank\": 0.0006921843463602832, \"text\": \"Gerard\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barksdale_Organization\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barksdale_Organization\"}, {\"begin\": 1129, \"end\": 1139, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Socialism\", \"score\": 0.5150124471160095, \"rank\": 0.8016368027170513, \"text\": \"socialists\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Socialism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Socialism\"}, {\"begin\": 1154, \"end\": 1157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Federation_Party\", \"score\": 0.9999953416392418, \"rank\": 3.840724037003097e-06, \"text\": \"NFP\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Federation_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Federation_Party\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If that was to happen, then there is a good chance that France can have a centrist coalition spanning left to right (amidst plenty of personal and policy disagreements).\", \"from\": 1160, \"to\": 1329, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1216, \"end\": 1222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.7508499543511039, \"rank\": 0.3293653420772698, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Before that happens, there needs to be a mini-crisis - possibly around economic policy - where the La France Insoumise - can be discredited.\", \"from\": 1330, \"to\": 1470, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This points to more volatility.\", \"from\": 1471, \"to\": 1502, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As it stands, the NFT group is trying to come up with a unified proposal for prime minister (official it is the president who picks the PM).\", \"from\": 1503, \"to\": 1643, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1521, \"end\": 1524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Non-fungible_token\", \"score\": 0.9999988353276837, \"rank\": 1.1646735898122333e-06, \"text\": \"NFT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Non-fungible_token\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Non-fungible_token\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile the RN (Rassemblement) remain marginalised and are positioning themselves as the party of the people (versus the elites).\", \"from\": 1645, \"to\": 1776, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In sum, the formation of a durable government will take more time, potentially to late August, and may also require more volatility.\", \"from\": 1778, \"to\": 1910, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A centrist coalition is a possibility, the issue is what kind of political strife is required to fuse it.\", \"from\": 1911, \"to\": 2016, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the meantime, the Olympics (and summer holidays) will take centre stage in France.\", \"from\": 2017, \"to\": 2102, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2095, \"end\": 2101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.7508499543511039, \"rank\": 0.3293653420772698, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}]}]}"